### Configuration Directory (optional)
## Directory KiwiSSH reads its configuration from (kiwissh.yaml, ssh_profiles.yaml, vendors/).
## Defaults to /config in Docker, or the bundled backend/config directory on bare-metal installs.
# KIWISSH_CONFIG_DIR=/config

### Local Testing Mode (optional)
## Set to true to use local test paths for easier mock-device testing
## Set to false for production with real SSH devices
##
## Instead of connecting to real devices via SSH, this reads configs
## from the tests/devices/ folder. Each device has a config.txt file
## that acts as the current running configuration.
##
## When KIWISSH_LOCAL_TEST_MODE=true:
##   - Config from: config/
##   - Device source is read from active kiwissh.yaml -> sources section
##   - Backups to: git.local_path
# KIWISSH_LOCAL_TEST_MODE=false

### Timezone Configuration (optional)
## Set timezone for logs and timestamps. Use IANA timezone format (e.g., Europe/Berlin, UTC, America/New_York)
## If not set, defaults to UTC. Database timestamps are always stored in UTC regardless of this setting.
# TZ=Europe/Berlin
